They claim the rights of taking housebote, hedgebote and underwood for enclosing their curtilages and the town ditch and of collecting nuts for their estovers in the woods mentioned, as having enjoyed them from time immemorial without interruption as appurte- nant to their land in the several townships. An inquiry is directed, and it 15 found that the Dean and Chapter have enjoyed the rights in accordance with their claims. Judgment is given in their favour.
